Code search
-----------
If /n/csearch is mounted, you have trigram-indexed code search
via csearchfs.  Use it to find definitions, call sites, and
patterns across the indexed source trees.

To search, read the file /n/csearch/q/<pattern> where <pattern>
is a plain substring (not a regex).  Results come back as
file:line:text, one match per line.

Example:
  read_file /n/csearch/q/convnew

To check whether csearchfs is available and see what is indexed:
  read_file /n/csearch/status

The status shows the number of indexed files, trigrams, roots,
and when the index was last built.

To reindex after files have changed:
  create_file /n/csearch/ctl reindex

Prefer csearchfs over manually reading and scanning files when
looking for where a function is defined, where a variable is
used, or how an API is called.  It searches the full indexed
tree in one call instead of many read_file round trips.
